    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, but that's kinda a vague answer. when people talk about 'originalism' vs 'living constitutionalism', it feels like one is based on actual history and the other is just whatever judges want it to be at the time. wouldn't you say originalism is a more rigorous legal method because it relies on the text as it was written?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
